<org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmi:id="-XTDkkkdM3l09L834EIInWg" name="cots_manage_receipt_of_package,_yycHT-wiEd-sjp03to1LnQ" guid="-XTDkkkdM3l09L834EIInWg" version="7.1.0">
  <sections xmi:id="_yycHUuwiEd-sjp03to1LnQ" name="Monitor COTS Package Delivery Schedule" guid="_yycHUuwiEd-sjp03to1LnQ">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;a id=&quot;MonitorCOTSPackageDeliverySchedule&quot; name=&quot;MonitorCOTSPackageDeliverySchedule&quot;>&lt;/a> &#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Maintain communication with the COTS package vendor by providing a contact for the vendor to resolve any queries or&#xD;
    notify of any problems arising. Any serious problems, particularly where delays to the delivery schedule are involved,&#xD;
    should be brought to the attention of project management.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Confirm delivery schedule with COTS package vendor one or two weeks before delivery is due.&#xD;
&lt;/p></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_yycHU-wiEd-sjp03to1LnQ" name="Prepare COTS Package Installation Plan" guid="_yycHU-wiEd-sjp03to1LnQ">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;a id=&quot;PrepareCOTSPackageInstallationPlan&quot; name=&quot;PrepareCOTSPackageInstallationPlan&quot;>&lt;/a> &#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Plan the installation of the COTS package, including:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Delivery and installation timetable&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Responsibility for installation&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Training prerequisites&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Installation testing (this is not intended as a comprehensive product test but as a minimum test to ensure that the&#xD;
        COTS package works as installed)&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The COTS package installation plan will be included as part of the installation artifacts.&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;/p></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_yycHUOwiEd-sjp03to1LnQ" name="Define Product Acceptance Criteria" guid="_yycHUOwiEd-sjp03to1LnQ">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;a id=&quot;DefineProductAcceptanceCriteria&quot; name=&quot;DefineProductAcceptanceCriteria&quot;>&lt;/a> &#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Describe in the &quot;Product Acceptance Criteria&quot; section of the product acceptance plan&amp;nbsp;the set of acceptance&#xD;
    criteria that will be followed to formally record what was delivered by the vendor and what was accepted by the&#xD;
    acquiring organization.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The product acceptance criteria is likely to ensure the following:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        The correct COTS package was delivered&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        All required documentation was provided: &#xD;
        &lt;ul>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
                href=&quot;./../../practice.tech.cots_dev.base-ibm/workproducts/cots_vendor_deployment_unit_550569FF.html&quot;&#xD;
                guid=&quot;_yycHMOwiEd-sjp03to1LnQ&quot;>Vendor Deployment Unit&lt;/a> &#xD;
                &lt;ul>&#xD;
                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                        Package Build&#xD;
                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                        Package Support Material&#xD;
                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                        Package Training Material&#xD;
                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                        Package Release Notes&#xD;
                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                        Package Installation Artifacts&#xD;
                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                        Package Bill of Materials&#xD;
                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                &lt;/ul>&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Guarantees or warranties&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Maintenance documents&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
        &lt;/ul>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Tools for carrying out maintenance tasks were provided&lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_yycHUewiEd-sjp03to1LnQ" name="Take Delivery of COTS Package" guid="_yycHUewiEd-sjp03to1LnQ">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;a id=&quot;TakeDeliveryofCOTSPackage&quot; name=&quot;TakeDeliveryofCOTSPackage&quot;>&lt;/a> &#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Using the criteria set out in the &quot;Product Acceptance Criteria&quot; section of the product acceptance plan&amp;nbsp;artifact,&#xD;
    check that the delivery is correct, complete, and intact. Copies of documents such as purchase order, delivery notes,&#xD;
    and packing slip should be retained.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;br /></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <purpose>&lt;a id=&quot;Top&quot; name=&quot;Top&quot;>&lt;/a> &#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        To monitor and process the delivery of the COTS package(s) and to plan the installation and acceptance of the COTS&#xD;
        package(s)&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></purpose>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
